How has it already been one week since Beckham was born?! One week ago today I did the hardest thing I’ve ever done and I’m so proud of myself, my body and my baby. Now that I’ve had time to process everything I had an amazing birth. I went in at 1pm on Thursday, May 11th and was induced. Since I was already 4cm dilated and 60% effaced I got to go straight to the Pitocin. I got the epidural shortly after. Epidural unfortunately didn’t take to my right leg but I didn’t feel any pain there so it was totally fine. Just a weird feeling! Baby Becks head was crooked so we had to move me around in all sorts of positions to get him into the right position! I labored for 10 hours and was finally dilated to a 10 and his head was in position so  it was time to push. I practice pushed with a nurse for about an hour and a half and I was completely exhausted which I know is normal. Finally with a couple big pushes I was able to get him to crown!!! I had to labor down and they called the doctor and she came shortly after and we pushed through 5 contractions and baby Becks was finally born May 12th at 1:33am and ready to take on the world. William was there for everything which was the most important thing to me and that’s why I was induced at 39 weeks. Will cut the umbilical cord too!! I’m so thankful for his love and support during it all. Also my birth team and support system was absolutely amazing and I’m so beyond thankful for all of them! I’ve been through a roller coaster of emotions but I’m beyond blessed to be healthy and recovering and to be taking care of a very healthy baby. Time is already flying by and I’m cherishing every moment. If you made it this far thanks for reading our birth story 🩵 #birthstory
